================================================================================
1. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
================================================================================

CONCEPT
-------
A single agent handles 88 service request types. Service definitions, field
schemas, and conditional rules all live in Dataverse. Adaptive cards for the
Form path are pre-built and cached on the Service record, rebuilt automatically
when definitions change. Quick Chat uses a Generative Answers loop grounded by
a per-service schema document in SharePoint. Adding a new service requires only
a data operation and a schema file upload — no topic changes.

FLOW SUMMARY
------------
  User opens agent
    └─ Conversational Start
         ├─ PA: Get Service List → Service picker card
         └─ Mode picker card (Quick Chat / Form)
              ├─ Quick Chat Topic
              │    ├─ Generative Answers loop (SharePoint schema knowledge)
              │    ├─ Completion detection (JSON with "complete": true)
              │    └─ PA: Submit Request → Dataverse
              └─ Form Topic
                   ├─ Read sbs_cardjson from sbs_Service record
                   ├─ Render pre-built adaptive card
                   └─ PA: Submit Request → Dataverse

CARD LIFECYCLE
--------------
  sbs_ServiceField / sbs_Field row changed
    └─ Trigger flow sets sbs_cardbuildstatus = "Pending"
  
  Nightly scheduled flow (e.g. 11 PM)
    └─ Queries all Pending service records
         └─ Calls SRA - Card Builder child flow per service
              └─ Writes built card JSON back to sbs_Service
                   └─ Sets status to Built or Failed

  Override path:
    If sbs_cardoverridejson is populated on sbs_Service,
    Card Builder returns it directly without generating.

GLOBAL VARIABLES (Copilot Studio)
----------------------------------
  Global.SelectedServiceId      Number   Dataverse service record ID
  Global.SelectedServiceName    Text     Display name e.g. "Just Print Me"
  Global.SelectedRequestType    Text     Payload key e.g. "JustPrintMe"
  Global.SelectedMode           Text     "QuickChat" or "Form"

================================================================================
2. SHAREPOINT SETUP
================================================================================

Create a SharePoint document library named: Service Schemas

For each service, upload a markdown (.md) file named by RequestType:
  Example: JustPrintMe.md

Content of each file should be the Output Schema Contract document for that
service — field definitions, valid values, conditional rules, and payload
schema. This is the knowledge source for the Quick Chat Generative Answers node.

The Generative Answers node is configured at agent level to use this SharePoint
library as a knowledge source. Dynamic instruction injection references
Global.SelectedRequestType to focus the node on the correct service file.

Naming convention is critical. The file name must exactly match the
sbs_requesttype value in the sbs_Service Dataverse record.

================================================================================
3. DATAVERSE TABLE SCHEMAS
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TABLE: sbs_Service
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Display Name: Service
Description:  Registry of all available request services

Columns:
  sbs_serviceid          Autonumber     Primary key
  sbs_name               Text(100)      Service display name
  sbs_description        Text(500)      Short description shown in service picker
  sbs_requesttype        Text(100)      JSON payload requestType value.
                                        Must match SharePoint schema filename.
  sbs_cardjson           Text(Max)      Pre-built adaptive card JSON for Form path.
                                        Populated and maintained by Card Builder flow.
  sbs_cardoverridejson   Text(Max)      If populated, Card Builder serves this
                                        directly and skips generation. Use for
                                        services requiring bespoke card layouts.
  sbs_cardlastupdated    DateTime       Timestamp of last successful card build.
  sbs_cardbuildstatus    Choice         Pending | Building | Built | Failed
                                        Default: Pending

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TABLE: sbs_Field
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Display Name: Field
Description:  Reusable field definitions shared across services

Columns:
  sbs_fieldid            Autonumber     Primary key
  sbs_fieldname          Text(100)      JSON key name. Must match payload schema exactly.
  sbs_displayname        Text(200)      Human-readable label shown in forms and chat
  sbs_fieldtype          Choice         Text | Number | Boolean | DateTime | Choice | URL
  sbs_validvalues        Text(2000)     JSON array of strings. Populated for Choice type only.
                                        Example: ["BlackWhite","Colour"]
  sbs_section            Text(100)      Payload section: root | charging | supply |
                                        printSpecifications | return
  sbs_helptext           Text(500)      Helper text shown below field in form card

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TABLE: sbs_ServiceField
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Display Name: Service Field
Description:  Junction table. Maps fields to services with ordering and
              conditional display rules.

Columns:
  sbs_servicefieldid       Autonumber       Primary key
  sbs_serviceid            Lookup(Service)  Related service record
  sbs_fieldid              Lookup(Field)    Related field definition
  sbs_isrequired           Boolean          Base required flag.
                                            Does not encode conditional requirements —
                                            those are handled via sbs_isconditional.
  sbs_displayorder         Integer          Render order. Use increments of 10
                                            to allow future insertions without renumber.
  sbs_isconditional        Boolean          True if this field only appears when a
                                            parent field condition is met.
  sbs_conditionalonfield   Text(100)        fieldname of the controlling field.
                                            Stores string name, not lookup ID, so PA
                                            can evaluate without a second query.
  sbs_conditionalvalue     Text(200)        Value(s) that trigger display of this field.
                                            Pipe-separated for OR conditions.
                                            Example: "HandDelivered|InternalMail"

